FBIS3-31118 "dreeu031_i_94016" FBIS-EEU-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Izetbegovic Comments on Talks With Churkin AU1502144194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 15 Feb 94 AU1502144194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] In the course of the day, President Izetbegovic also met with Russian envoy Vitaliy Churkin to discuss the same issues. Here is what the president told correspondents about the content of the talks: [Begin Izetbegovic recording] It is (?particularly) interesting that Mr. Churkin said that even Russia supports -- so he says -- the lifting of the Sarajevo siege, that it supports this position. I took the chance to warn Mr. Churkin of the offensive, the Serb offensive up there in Bihac, [words indistinct], and I asked him to use his influence to immediately stop the offensive. He promised to do what he could to have the attack stopped. [end recording]
